text: Daniel Milton Newhouse (born July 10, 1955) is an American politician and agricultural scientist. He is a member of the United States House of Representatives for since 2015. Newhouse was director of the Washington Department of Agriculture and as a member of the Washington House of Representatives from 2009 to 2013. He is a member of the Republican Party. Newhouse announced his support for the second impeachment of Donald Trump on January 13, 2021, following the 2021 storming of the United States Capitol. ==References== Category:1955 births Category:Living people Category:United States representatives from Washington Category:Scientists from Washington (state) Category:Republican Party (United States) politicians
